observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management agreed to:
Follow procedures on the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances provided in COA Circular 2020-006;
Require the maintenance of property ledger cards by the accounting office, to be reconciled with the property cards;
Direct the General Services Office to verify and validate the items under the Buildings account recorded in the accounting reports but not reported in the RPCPPE, as well as the donated motor vehicles, and adjust the property reports accordingly; and
Require the Accounting Office to verify and validate the items reported in the RPCPPE but not recorded in the accounting reports, and adjust the accounting reports accordingly.

We recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:
determine and identify the funds received for specific purpose and effect the appropriate adjustments on the Other Payables  and Trust Liabilities account, to come up with correct balances;
revert to the unappropriated surplus the revenues and other collections with lapsed purposes or have become irrelevant;
determine the fund transfers with completed projects or activities and return the balances to the respective source agencies and for projects still on going, reclassify from Other Payables to Trust Liabilities; and
review funds used in charging the employees’ accounts and adjust accordingly. In case of over-remittance that resulted in abnormal balances, reclassify said payables to Due to Officers and Employees.
